		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />"The 65c816 has a far better Mhz/performance ratio"
<br />
<br />...and it would've had an even better Mhz/performance ratio, if only developers didn't intentionally sabatoge their SNES games for the sole purpose of marketing the Genesis version to an older "hardcore gamer" audience, and marketing the SNES version to a "kiddy" audience, who wanted easier slower paced games.
<br />
<br />That's the one thing about buying gaming hardware. (both PC and video game systems)  System specs don't mean shit when stupid marketing politics get in the way of what kind of games they make on the system.  
<br />
<br />The SNES could've used a 500 khz Z80, and there wouldn't have been a difference.

		

